This paper is focused on improving the state-of-the-art semi-supervised learning algorithm, MixMatch, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image classification datasets such as CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and SVHN, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of active learning techniques, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper provides an empirical analysis of the cost trade-off between labeled and unlabeled data, which could also place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
